據報導紐約尼克因林書豪在場上的表現而成功促成一場糾紛的結束，這場糾紛曾讓{{tsl|en|Time Warner Cable|時代華納有線電視}}的客戶在48天內無法收看紐約尼克的比賽和其他{{tsl|en|MSG (TV network)||MSG電視網}}的節目<ref>{{cite news|last1=Beck|first1=Howard|last2=Sandomir|first2=Richard|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/02/18/sports/time-warner-cable-and-garden-resolve-dispute.html|title=Time Warner and MSG Network End Their Cable Dispute|work=The New York Times|date=2012-02-18|accessdate=2012-02-18|page=D5|archive-date=2012-02-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120218002741/http://www.nytimes.com/2012/02/18/sports/time-warner-cable-and-garden-resolve-dispute.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。球隊母公司{{tsl|en|Madison Square Garden Company|麥迪遜廣場花園公司}}的市值在2月增加了2.5億美元，到2012年7月共增加了6億美元{{r|silver_07162012}}。紐約尼克開始迅速銷售林書豪17號球衣和T恤的複製品，其網路商店的銷售額和流量增加了3000%以上<ref>{{cite news |last=McCarthy |first=Michael |title=Lin carrying Knicks and creating a $14 million brand |date=2012-02-14 |newspaper=USA Today |accessdate=2020-09-04 |url=https://usatoday30.usatoday.com/sports/basketball/nba/story/2012-02-14/Lin-carrying-Knicks-and-creating-a-14-million-brand/53092494/1 |archive-date=2020-03-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325190221/https://usatoday30.usatoday.com/sports/basketball/nba/story/2012-02-14/Lin-carrying-Knicks-and-creating-a-14-million-brand/53092494/1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。林書豪的球衣在2012年2月4日當周成為聯盟網路上最暢銷的球衣，紐約尼克也同時成為最暢銷的球隊；球隊在2月10日開始銷售林書豪的商品，在麥迪遜廣場花園的一個紀念品攤位，於比賽開打前就已售罄相關商品{{r|mahoney20120211}}。他的商品佔據紐約尼克商店的陳列空間，而球隊當時高薪球員，卡梅隆·安东尼、阿玛雷·斯塔德迈尔和泰森·钱德勒的商品則被移至銷售架上<ref name="silver_07162012">{{cite news |last=Silver |first=Nate |title=Keeping Lin Should Make Financial Sense for the Knicks |date=2012-07-16 |newspaper=The New York Times |accessdate=2020-09-04 |url=https://fivethirtyeight.com/features/keeping-lin-should-make-financial-sense-for-the-knicks/ |archive-date=2016-11-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161118162704/http://fivethirtyeight.com/features/keeping-lin-should-make-financial-sense-for-the-knicks/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。他的球衣在2月和3月是全NBA銷量最好的，在2011年5月到2012年4月的一年期間裡，林書豪的球衣銷量位居聯盟第二名，僅次於[[德里克·罗斯|德里克·罗斯]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Zwerling |first=Jared |title=Jeremy Lin No. 2 on NBA jersey sales list |date=2012-04-26 |work=ESPN |accessdate=2020-09-04 |url=https://www.espn.com/blog/new-york/knicks/post/_/id/17740/jeremy-lin-no-2-on-nba-jersey-sales-list |archive-date=2020-05-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200525075718/https://www.espn.com/blog/new-york/knicks/post/_/id/17740/jeremy-lin-no-2-on-nba-jersey-sales-list |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Derrick Rose, Jeremy Lin top sellers |date=2012-04-26 |title=Derrick Rose, Jeremy Lin top sellers |publisher=ESPN |accessdate=2020-09-04 |url=https://www.espn.com/nba/story/_/id/7857542/derrick-rose-chicago-bulls-jeremy-lin-new-york-knicks-top-nba-jersey-sales |archive-date=2020-05-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200525065735/https://www.espn.com/nba/story/_/id/7857542/derrick-rose-chicago-bulls-jeremy-lin-new-york-knicks-top-nba-jersey-sales |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Levinson |first=Mason |author2=Novy-Williams, Eben |title=Jeremy Lin Drives Sales of Knicks' Merchandise as MSG Shares Reach Record |date=2012-02-13 |publisher=Bloomberg |accessdate=2020-09-04 |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2012-02-13/jeremy-lin-drives-knicks-sales-as-msg-shares-climb-to-record |archive-date=2016-03-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306145307/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2012-02-13/jeremy-lin-drives-knicks-sales-as-msg-shares-climb-to-record |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[Nike|Nike]]和[[Adidas|Adidas]]都推出與林書豪相關的運動服裝，並估計他的名氣將有助於在中國大陸的銷售<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.oregonlive.com/business/2012/02/jeremy_lin_craze_big_news_at_n.html|title=Jeremy Lin craze is welcome news at Nike, Adidas|work=The Oregonian|date=2012-02-22|accessdate=2012-02-23|author=Brettman, Allan|archive-date=2019-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190305134159/https://www.oregonlive.com/business/2012/02/jeremy_lin_craze_big_news_at_n.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。他受歡迎的程度與[[姚明|姚明]]退役後NBA在中國大陸的人氣增長有關；NBA球賽在中國大陸的電視和網路觀眾人數比前一個賽季增長了39%<ref>{{cite news |title='Linsanity' a boon for NBA in China |date=2012-02-17 |publisher=ESPN |agency=Associated Press |accessdate=2020-09-04 |url=https://www.espn.com/new-york/nba/story/_/id/7584905/new-york-knicks-jeremy-lin-spurring-growth-nba-china-yao-ming-happy |archive-date=2020-05-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200525064112/https://www.espn.com/new-york/nba/story/_/id/7584905/new-york-knicks-jeremy-lin-spurring-growth-nba-china-yao-ming-happy |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

